<title>JAPAN: Mazda shares jump on solid earnings.</title>
<headline>Mazda shares jump on solid earnings.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Mazda Motor Corp surged in late morning trade on Friday, due to the announcement of solid earnings just before the close of the morning session, traders said.</p>
<p>At midday, the automaker's shares were up 24 yen at 365. Its turnover was 497,000 shares.  </p>
<p>Mazda said its parent current profit totalled 13.90 billion yen in 1996/97, up sharply from the previous year's 1.23 billion yen. The profit figure was larger than earlier estimates by industry analysts.</p>
